

{{!< main}}

<main class="container">
    <!-- Static sections -->
    <section>
        <h2>Why MVC is so important</h2>
        <p>MVC, or Model-View-Controller, is a design pattern...</p>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Authentication vs Authorization</h2>
        <p>Authentication is the process of verifying who a user is, while authorization is the process of verifying what they have access to. These processes are fundamental in security systems to ensure that users can only access the resources they are permitted to.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Object-Relational Mapping</h2>
        <p>Object-Relational Mapping, or ORM, is a technique that converts data between incompatible type systems using object-oriented programming languages. It creates a "virtual object database" that can be used from within the programming language.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Dynamic section for blog posts -->
    <section>
        <h2>Latest Posts</h2>
        {{#each posts}}
            <article>
                <h3><a href="/posts/{{this.id}}">{{this.title}}</a></h3>
                <p>{{truncate this.content 150}} <a href="/posts/{{this.id}}">Read more...</a></p>
            </article>
        {{else}}
            <p>No posts to display.</p>
        {{/each}}
    </section>
</main>
